title: Add lastError to Sinon-Chrome
body:
Adds the lastError property to Sinon-Chrome. Docs for the real property are at https://developer.chrome.com/extensions/runtime#property-lastError

This wasn't included before as the rest of the API is just the defined stubs, whereas lastError is a property that's initially undefined, and which you'd add in test code when you want to simulate an error. It doesn't actually exist in the SinonChrome codebase, interestingly, because it's only value is as a place to attach a property. Free to do that in JavaScript, but needs to be part of the interface to work in TypeScript.

title: Replace Stream#_transform()s with single method with chunk: any
body:
When a stream.Transform is fed from a stream that has `{objectMode: true}`, the `Stream#_transform(chunk, encoding, callback)` method will not be called with chunks that are strings or Buffers.

Simply adding a `_transform()` variant with `chunk: any` does not satisfy the TypeScript compiler for some reason.

I'd prefer type parameterizing the whole `stream.Transform` class with the type of the chunks it will deal with, but this change is smaller, and, I imagine, less contentious.

title: Bring react and react-addons together to make it easier for other libraries.
body:
Bring react and react-addons together to make it easier for other libraries to depend on just 'react' and the user can optionally use `require('react/addons')` without conflict.  Uses ES6 modules and re-exports to accomplish this.

This has a breaking change in that the additional types in react-addons are now under the `.addons.` module.  For example, where it used to be `React.LinkedStateMixin` it now is `React.addons.LinkedStateMixin`.  This is only true for the interface definition.  The actual mixin variable was already `React.addons.LinkedStateMixin`.

title: updated tv4 to fully match 1.2.5
body:
wrapped  interfaces in a module, removed prefixes
because of addition of module, which breaks existing naming, versioned the existing files as one version back from current 1.2.5

Note that old naming from within client code was for example _TV4MultiResult_ but is now _tv4.MultiResult_.
Users updating to the new one will have to update their code. If they don't want to, they can switch to the 1.2.4 version.

Also, note the change of the type _TV4Error_ to _ValidationError_, as dropping the prefix leads to a name collision with the native type _Error_. I chose _ValidationError_ as that's what's used in the tv4 library.

As a separate matter: I thought it would be better to ask the package maintainer to add these TypeScript declarations directly to their package under ./typings/tv4, in order to be compatible with _tsd_. Please see my Pull Request for tv4: https://github.com/geraintluff/tv4/pull/214.  Also, note that I added a test: 
testTypeScriptDecls: 'tsc --noImplicitAny --noEmit ./typings/tv4/tv4-tests.ts'

I'd appreciate hearing your thoughts on how to best manage declaration files for a module.
